<para id="RM000000W89010X" category="C" type-id="302GH" name-id="AX0YW-01" from="200601">
<dtccode>P2759</dtccode>
<dtcname>Torque Converter Clutch Pressure Control Solenoid Control Circuit Electrical (Shift Solenoid Valve SLU)</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000W89010X_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000037000000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The amount of current flow to the solenoid is controlled by the (*) duty ratio of the TCM output signal. The higher the duty ratio becomes, the higher the lock-up hydraulic pressure becomes during the lock-up operation.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C133227E01" width="7.106578999in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>(*) Duty Ratio</ptxt>
<ptxt>The duty ratio is the ratio of the period of continuity in one cycle. For example, if A is the period of continuity in one cycle, and B is the period of non-continuity, then Duty Ratio = A/(A+B) x 100 (%).</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" align="center" colwidth="1.42in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" align="center" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>P2759</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Open or short is detected in shift solenoid valve SLU circuit for 1 second or more while driving (1-trip detection logic).</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="left">
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Open or short in shift solenoid valve SLU circuit</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Shift solenoid valve SLU</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>TCM</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000W89010X_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000037100000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>When an open or short in a shift solenoid valve (SLU) circuit is detected, the TCM determines there is a malfunction. The TCM will turn on the MIL and store this DTC.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
